tigase.jaxmpp.core.client.xmpp.modules

Interface InitializingModule

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractIQModule, AbstractStanzaExtendableModule, AbstractStanzaModule, AdHocCommansModule, AuthModule, BookmarksModule, CapabilitiesModule, DiscoveryModule, EntityTimeModule, FlexibleOfflineMessageRetrieval, InBandRegistrationModule, MessageCarbonsModule, MessageModule, MucModule, NonSaslAuthModule, PingModule, PresenceModule, PubSubModule, RosterModule, SoftwareVersionModule, VCardModule

    public interface InitializingModule
    Interface should be implemented by module that need to be informed about its state in XmppModulesManager.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void afterRegister()
      Called when module is registered.
      void beforeRegister()
      Called just before registration module in XmppModulesManager .
      void beforeUnregister()
      Called when module is unregistered.

    • Method Detail

      • afterRegister

        void afterRegister()
        Called when module is registered. At this moment module is formally registered and it is part of client.

      • beforeRegister

        void beforeRegister()
        Called just before registration module in XmppModulesManager . It is good place to check if module is initialized properly.

      • beforeUnregister

        void beforeUnregister()
        Called when module is unregistered.
